@page "/docs/splitter"
@using MudX.Docs.Splitter
@using MudX.Docs.Examples

<PageTitle>Splitter</PageTitle>

<DocsPage Headline="Splitter">
    <ChildContent>
        <DocsPageHeader>
            <Description>
                A flexible splitter component for building resizable layouts. It supports both horizontal and vertical panels, and you can fully customize 
                its appearance and behavior by providing your own <CodeInline Tag="false">SplitterTemplate</CodeInline>.
            </Description>
        </DocsPageHeader>

        <DocsPageSection Title="Basic Usage">
            <Description>
                By default, <CodeInline>MudXSplitter</CodeInline> uses <CodeInline Tag="false">SplitterDirection.Horizontal</CodeInline>. It renders an 8px-wide splitter 
                bar with 10px of margin on all four sides. The <CodeInline Tag="false">StartSplitter</CodeInline> pane appears on the left, and the 
                <CodeInline Tag="false">EndSplitter</CodeInline> pane appears on the right.
            </Description>
            <ChildContent>
                <SectionContent Codes="@SplitterBasicExampleCode.Files">
                    <SplitterBasicExample />
                </SectionContent>
            </ChildContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

        <DocsPageSection Title="Vertical">
            <Description>
                To create a vertical splitter, set <CodeInline Tag="false">Direction</CodeInline> to <CodeInline Tag="false">SplitterDirection.Vertical</CodeInline>. 
                In this case, the <CodeInline Tag="false">StartSplitter</CodeInline> pane appears at the top, and the <CodeInline Tag="false">EndSplitter</CodeInline> 
                pane appears at the bottom.
            </Description>
            <ChildContent>
                <SectionContent Codes="@SplitterVerticalExampleCode.Files">
                    <SplitterVerticalExample />
                </SectionContent>
            </ChildContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

        <DocsPageSection Title="Customization">
            <Description>
                You can customize <CodeInline>MudXSplitter</CodeInline> in two ways:<br />
                Apply CSS for small style adjustments (e.g., splitter size or color).<br />
                Provide a custom <CodeInline Tag="false">SplitterTemplate</CodeInline> to fully control the splitter’s appearance and behavior.
            </Description>
            <ChildContent>
                <SectionContent Codes="@SplitterCustomizeExampleCode.Files">
                    <SplitterCustomizeExample />
                </SectionContent>
            </ChildContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

        <DocsPageSection Title="Sizing">
            <Description>
                By default the Splitter component runs 100% width and height of its container. You can set a fixed height or width using the 
                <CodeInline Tag=false>Height</CodeInline> or <CodeInline Tag=false>Width</CodeInline> parameters. <br />
                Each pane of the splitter can be sized according to your layout needs. You can: <br />
                Set a minimum size for the <CodeInline Tag=false>StartSplitter</CodeInline> and <CodeInline Tag=false>EndSplitter</CodeInline> panes.<br />
                Bind the current size of the <CodeInline Tag=false>StartSplitter</CodeInline> pane to a variable.
            </Description>
            <ChildContent>
                <SectionContent Codes="@SplitterSizingExampleCode.Files">
                    <SplitterSizingExample />
                </SectionContent>
            </ChildContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

        <DocsPageSection Title="Nesting">
            <Description>
                Splitters can be nested to create complex layouts. For example, you can use a horizontal splitter for a sidebar and content area, 
                then place a vertical splitter inside the content area to divide an editor and a console. Nesting allows you to build multi-pane 
                interfaces similar to IDEs or dashboards.
            </Description>
            <ChildContent>
                <SectionContent Codes="@SplitterNestingExampleCode.Files">
                    <SplitterNestingExample />
                </SectionContent>
            </ChildContent>
        </DocsPageSection>

    </ChildContent>
    <ApiContent>
        <ApiSection ApiJson="MudXSplitter.api.json" />
    </ApiContent>

</DocsPage>

@code {
#pragma warning disable CS0414
    private static string __title__ = "Splitter";
#pragma warning restore CS0414
}